revision.text:
[[File:Constant Awashish - Assermentation.jpg|thumb|right|[[Constant Awashish]] during his swearing as the grand chief of the Conseil de la Nation Atikamekw, in the background the flag of the CNA]] The '''Conseil de la Nation Atikamekw''' (CNA) ([[French language|French]] for "Council of the Atikamekw Nation"), officially named '''Atikamekw Sipi - Conseil de la Nation Atikamekw''', is a [[tribal council]] in [[Quebec]], Canada. It is composed of the three [[Atikamekw]] [[Band governments|bands]]: [[Atikamekw of Manawan|Manawan]], [[Atikamekw of Opitciwan|Opitciwan]] and [[Wemotaci Atikamekw Council|Wemotaci]]. Together, the three bands have a total registered population of 7,747 members in 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fnp-ppn.aandc-aadnc.gc.ca/fnp/Main/Search/FNRegPopulation.aspx?BAND_NUMBER=78&lang=eng |title=Registered population {{!}} Les Atikamekw de Manawan |website=[[Indigenous and Northern Affairs Canada]] |access-date=29 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://fnp-ppn.aandc-aadnc.gc.ca/fnp/Main/Search/FNRegPopulation.aspx?BAND_NUMBER=79&lang=eng |title=Registered population {{!}} Atikamekw d'Opitciwan |website=[[Indigenous and Northern Affairs Canada]] |access-date=29 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://fnp-ppn.aandc-aadnc.gc.ca/fnp/Main/Search/FNRegPopulation.aspx?BAND_NUMBER=77&lang=eng |title=Registered Population {{!}} Conseil des Atikamekw de Wemotaci |website=[[Indigenous and Northern Affairs Canada]] |access-date=29 November 2016}}</ref> It is headquartered in [[La Tuque, Quebec]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fnp-ppn.aandc-aadnc.gc.ca/fnp/Main/Search/TCMain.aspx?TC_NUMBER=1064&lang=eng |title=Tribal Council Detail |website=[[Indigenous and Northern Affairs Canada]] |access-date=29 November 2016}}</ref> The role of the CNA is to officially represent all [[Atikamekw|Atikamekw Nehirowisiw]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Les Attikameks |website=[[Secrétariat aux affaires autochtones Québec]] |language=fr |url=http://www.autochtones.gouv.qc.ca/relations_autochtones/profils_nations/attikameks.htm |access-date=2 December 2016}}</ref> In September 2014, the CNA declared its sovereignty on its ancestral territory, the [[Nitaskinan]], covering approximately 80,000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ici.radio-canada.ca/nouvelle/683598/nation-atikamekw-declaration-souverainete-territoire |title=Les Atikamekw déclarent leur souveraineté |date=8 September 2014 |website=[[Radio-Canada|Radio-Canada.ca]] |access-date=29 November 2016 |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Pierre Trudel |title=Entrevue avec Constant Awashish, Grand Chef du Conseil de la Nation atikamekw |journal=Recherches amérindiennes au Québec |volume=44 |year=2014 |pages=119–121 |issn=1923-5151 |doi=10.7202/1027887ar |url=http://id.erudit.org/iderudit/1027887ar |language=fr}}</ref>
