{{Infobox settlement |name = Evenk Ethnic Sumu |native_name = 鄂温克民族苏木 |postal_code = 021512 |postal_code_type = [[Postal code of China|Postal code]] |pushpin_label = |pushpin_label_position = left |pushpin_map = China Inner Mongolia |settlement_type = [[Ethnic sumu]] |image_skyline = |image_caption = |image_size = |map_caption = Location in Inner Mongolia |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = [[China]] |subdivision_type1 = [[Province (China)|Province-level division]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Inner Mongolia]] |subdivision_type2 = [[Prefecture-level city]] |subdivision_name2 = [[Hulunbuir]] |subdivision_type3 = [[Banner (Inner Mongolia)|Banner]] |subdivision_name3 = [[Old Barag Banner]] |seat = |area_code = 0470 |area_total_km2 = 6037 |population_as_of = 2010 |population_density_km2 = auto |population_total = 2665 |coordinates = {{coord|49|47|28|N|120|05|21|E|region:CN-15|display=inline,title}} |elevation_m = 660 |timezone = [[China Standard Time|China Standard]] |utc_offset = +8 |website = }}
The '''Evenk Ethnic Sumu''' ({{zh|s=鄂温克民族苏木 |t=鄂溫克民族蘇木 |p=Èwēnkè Mínzúsūmù}}) is an administrative subdivision in the northeastern part of [[Old Barag Banner]] in [[Hulunbuir]], [[Inner Mongolia]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.stats.gov.cn/tjbz/cxfldm/2011/15/07/150725.html |script-title=zh:2011年统计用区划代码和城乡划分代码：陈巴尔虎旗 |publisher = National Bureau of Statistics of the People's Republic of China |language = Chinese |accessdate = 2013-01-19}}</ref> It has an area of {{convert|6037|km2|abbr=on}} and, {{asof|2010|lc=y}}, a population of 2665 of which 1560 (54.4%) are ethnic [[Evenks]].<ref>{{cite web | publisher = 内蒙古自治区民族宗教网 | script-title = zh:陈巴尔虎旗鄂温克苏木 | url = http://www.nmgmzw.gov.cn/Article.aspx?Id=20802 | date = 2010-05-01 | accessdate = 2013-01-19 | language = zh | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110109015929/http://www.nmgmzw.gov.cn/Article.aspx?Id=20802 | archivedate = 2011-01-09 | df = }}</ref>
{{Asof|2010}}, it is the only "ethnic [[Sumu (administrative division)|sumu]]" in China; the sumu is a type of administrative unit at the [[Township (People's Republic of China)|township]] (fourth) level only found in Inner Mongolia, equivalent to [[ethnic township]]s in other parts of China.
It is located on grassland {{convert|68|km}} north-northeast of the urban area of Hulunbuir.
