'''Mamadama Bangoura''' (born November 10, 1993) is a [[Guinea]]n [[judoka]].
==Career== She competed at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Judo at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Women's 63 kg|women's 63 kg]] event, in which she was eliminated by [[Estefania García]] in the first round.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mamadama Bangoura |url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/mamadama-bangoura |website=Rio 2016 |accessdate=August 20, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820143639/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/mamadama-bangoura |archivedate=August 20, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Women -63 kg - Standings |url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/judo-standings-ju-women-63-kg |website=Rio 2016 |accessdate=August 20, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820143738/https://www.rio2016.com/en/judo-standings-ju-women-63-kg |archivedate=August 20, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> She was the flag bearer for Guinea at the [[2016 Summer Olympics Parade of Nations|Parade of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rio 2016 Olympic Ceremony - Flag Bearers|url=https://stillmed.olympic.org/media/Document%20Library/OlympicOrg/News/2016/08/2016-08-05-Rio-2016-Opening-Ceremony-Flag-Bearers.pdf#_ga=1.141545717.655653539.1470508014|publisher=International Olympic Committee|accessdate=August 20, 2016}}</ref>
Mamadama Bangoura did not return to Guinea after the 2016 Summer Olympics in Brazil, having disappeared after leaving a message saying she wanted to "try her luck" abroad.<ref>[http://www.latimes.com/sports/olympics/la-sp-oly-rio-2016-two-guinea-athletes-do-not-return-home-1472317295-htmlstory.html Two Guinea athletes do not return home after Rio Olympics]</ref>
