{{no footnotes|date=July 2017}} '''Pavlos Kouroupis''' (Greek: Παύλος Κουρούπης) was a [[Greece|Greek]] soldier born in 1929 in [[Kalamata]].
==Biography== Kouroupis was an officer in the [[Hellenic Army]], at the time of the [[Turkish invasion of Cyprus]] in 1974, he was a Lt. Colonel and CO of the 251st Battalion of the [[Cypriot National Guard]], the unit closest to the Turkish landing site. With his unit, he opposed the Turkish army at the [[Battle of Pentemili beachhead]], stalling its advance for two days. He was forced to retreat before vastly superior Turkish numbers. He was presumed dead during the defence of [[Keryneia]].
==See also== *[[List of people who disappeared mysteriously]]
==External links== *[http://www.missing-cy.org/cgi-bin/missing/gr_display_sn?447 Information about Kouroupis] {{el icon}}
