{{Infobox Politician | name = Ruhulla Akhundov | image = | caption = | birth_date ={{birth date|1897|01|1}} | birth_place = [[Shuvalan]], [[Baku Governorate]], [[Russian Empire]] | residence = | death_date = {{death date and age|1938|4|21|1897|1|1}} | death_place = | office= First Secretary of the [[Azerbaijan Communist Party]] | term_start = 1925 | term_end = 1926 | party = [[Communist Party of the Soviet Union]] | religion = | occupation = Publicist | majority = | spouse = Frida Naumovna Shlemovna | children = | website = | footnotes = }}
'''Ruhulla Akhundov''' ({{lang-az|Ruhulla Əli oğlu Axundov}}; 1 January 1897, [[Shuvalan]], [[Baku Governorate]], [[Russian Empire]] – 21 April 1938) was the [[Communism|communist]] leader of [[Azerbaijan SSR]] from 1925 to 1926, under the [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] leadership of [[Joseph Stalin]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Street Scenes from Yesteryear|url=http://www.azer.com/aiweb/categories/magazine/82_folder/82_articles/82_rezaguliyev.html|website=www.azer.com|accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:Ахундов, Рухулла Алиевич|url=http://seomonsta.ru/wathoe4/%D0%90%D1%85%D1%83%D0%BD%D0%B4%D0%BE%D0%B2,_%D0%A0%D1%83%D1%85%D1%83%D0%BB%D0%BB%D0%B0_%D0%90%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%B5%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%87|website=seomonsta.ru|accessdate=13 August 2014|language=Russian}}</ref>
==Arrest and execution== In 1938, he was arrested for "participation in terrorist activities" and sentenced to [[execution by firing squad]] by Military Tribunal. He was executed on April 21, 1938 at [[Butovo firing range]]. In 1959, he was posthumously rehabilitated by [[Military Collegium of the Supreme Court of the USSR]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ruhulla Əli oğlu Axundov|url=http://www.muallim.edu.az/arxiv/2011/23/17.htm|website=www.muallim.edu.az|accessdate=13 August 2014|language=Azerbaijani|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130820022735/http://www.muallim.edu.az/arxiv/2011/23/17.htm|archivedate=20 August 2013|df=}}</ref>
