{{Infobox film | name = Secrets of the Psychics | image = Secrets of the PsychicsVideo.jpg | caption = | director = | producer = [[Carl Charlson]] | writer = | starring = [[James Randi]] | music = | cinematography = | editing = | distributor = ''[[Nova (TV series)|NOVA]]'' | released = October 19, 1993 and March 28, 2000 | runtime = 60 minutes | rating = | country = United States | awards = | language = English | budget = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | ISBN = }}
"'''Secrets of the Psychics'''" was a PBS ''[[NOVA (TV series)|NOVA]]'' episode following [[James Randi]]'s work.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.csicop.org/webmaster/randi/ |title=James Randi on Secrets of the Psychics |accessdate = 2007-04-02 |last= |first= |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070203132904/http://www.csicop.org/webmaster/randi/ <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-02-03}}</ref> Also appearing in [[stock footage]] are [[Peter Popoff]], [[Uri Geller]], and many others.
In the program, "Randi argues that successful psychics depend on the willingness of their audiences to believe that what they see is the result of psychic powers."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/teachers/programs/2012_psychics.html |title=Secrets of the Psychics: Program Overview |accessdate = 2007-04-02 |last= |first= }}</ref>
This program is not to be confused with a later UK documentary ''Secrets of the Psychics'', which was transmitted under this title as well as ''[[Secrets of the Super Psychics]]''.
