'''Susan Massotty''' is an award-winning translator,  known for her translations of Dutch literary works into English. She translated ''[[The Diary of Anne Frank]]'' for the [[Everyman’s Library]]. She has also translated works by [[Kader Abdolah]], [[Cees Nooteboom]], [[Abdelkader Benali]] and [[Margriet de Moor]], among others. She won the [[Vondel Prize]] for Abdolah's 2000 novel ''My Father’s Notebook''.<ref>[https://www.wordswithoutborders.org/contributor/susan-massotty Bio]</ref> 

