{{Infobox football biography | name = Veronika Klechová | image = | caption = | fullname = Veronika Klechová | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1989|5|5}} | birth_place = [[Czechoslovakia]] | height = | currentclub = | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = | clubs1 = [[Slovan Bratislava (women)|Slovan Bratislava]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | nationalyears1 = 2006– | nationalteam1 = [[Slovakia women's national football team|Slovakia]] | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = }}
'''Veronika Klechová''' (born 5 May 1989) is a [[Slovakia|Slovak]] [[women's soccer|football]] [[midfielder]] currently playing in the [[Slovak Women's First League|Slovak First League]] for [[Slovan Bratislava (women)|Slovan Bratislava]],<ref>[http://www.futbalsfz.sk/oficialne-spravy/novinka/nominacia-reprezentacie-zien-na-kvalifikacne-zapasy-s-finskom.html SWNT call-up] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419094234/http://www.futbalsfz.sk/oficialne-spravy/novinka/nominacia-reprezentacie-zien-na-kvalifikacne-zapasy-s-finskom.html |date=April 19, 2012 }} vs. [[Finland women's national football team|Finland]] in the [[Slovak Football Association]]'s website</ref> with whom she has also played the [[UEFA Women's Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/womenschampionsleague/season=2012/clubs/player=101042/profile/index.html Profile]{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} in [[UEFA]]'s website</ref> She has been a member of the [[Slovakia women's national football team|Slovak national team]] since debuting at 17 in 2006.<ref>[http://es.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=265127/index.html Statistics] in [[FIFA]]'s website</ref>
When Klechová's partner [[Filip Kiss]] was [[Loan (sports)|loaned]] from [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] to [[Ross County F.C.|Ross County]] in January 2014, she made a similar move from [[Cardiff City Ladies F.C.|Cardiff City Ladies]] to [[Inverness City L.F.C.|Inverness City]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Inverness City Ladies FC signs Slovak international|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-highlands-islands-25669573|accessdate=31 August 2015|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=23 January 2014}}</ref>
